**[1841, 03-01] Ms.A.1.2.11.94**

JAC to WLG; Glasgow.

“I have never till my visit to this country realized the value of your
existence, nor the absolute need the world has for such spirits as
yourself.” [Having more success establishing Old Org in Scotland. Notes
that Cresson and Gurley are in the country promoting colonization, but
he says let them come and carry off pretended abolitionists, and that
colonizationism is not half as dangerous as new organizationism.]


